<ITEM>G. <HI>Earl of,</HI> Father of Lord G; his fir&s;t vi&s;it, with Lady Gertrude his &s;i&s;ter, to Mi&s;s Charlotte Grandi&s;on, on his &s;on's behalf, iv. 7 to 9. His earne&s;tne&s;s for his &s;on's &s;peedy marriage, iv. 81. Vi&s;its her a &s;e|cond time with lady Gertrude, iv. 83. Rejoices in her con&s;ent to marry his &s;on, iv. 84. His pre&s;ents to her, iv. 95. His letter urg|ing Lady G. to return from Northampton&s;hire, v. 119.</ITEM>
