<ITEM>KEELING family engaged in a law-&s;uit with the Mansfields, iv. 267. In a way of accommodation, v. 200, 201. Sir Charles Grandi&s;on's conferences on this &s;ubject with them and their friend Sir John Lambton, vi. 1, 2, &amp; &s;eq. In&s;olence of the younger Keeling, vi. 3. Accommodation brought forward, vi. 168. <HI>See</HI> Mansfield.</ITEM>
