<ITEM>LOWTHER, <HI>Mr.</HI> a &s;kilful &s;urgeon; his character from Sir Charles Grandi&s;on, iv. 63. 281. De&s;cribes his pa&s;&s;age over Mount Cenis, iv. 271 to 276. The &s;ucce&s;s of his art on Jeronymo, v. 78. His further character from Sir Charles; who expre&s;&s;es his de&s;ire of engaging him to fix in his neighbourhood, v. 235, 236. Sends an account to Sir Charles of the &s;tate of affairs in the family of Porretta &s;ince his depar|ture from Italy, vii. 62, 63. Returns Sir Charles's pre&s;ents, on be|ing amply rewarded by his patie&punc; vii. 63, 64. Arrives in England, and gives further particulars relating to Lady Clementina, vii. 75 to 77. Agrees to &s;ettle in Sir Charles's neighbourhood, vii. 96. Con|&s;ults the London phy&s;icians on the ca&s;e of Lady Clementina, vii. 257.</ITEM>
