<HI>Mode&s;ty</HI> is ea&s;ily alarmed, i. 50. A pure heart will be always pure, ibid. A mode&s;t man <HI>mu&s;t</HI> have merit, i. 104. 304. Mode&s;ty in a man gives an agreeable &s;elf-confidence to a woman, iii. 162. 168. All men, good and bad, admire Mode&s;ty in women: Shall women like men the wor&s;e for having that grace? iv. 13. Mode&s;ty and meekne&s;s characte|ri&s;tic qualities in women, iv. 93. <HI>See al&s;o</HI> iv. 131. &verbar; v. 275. &verbar; vi. 146.</ITEM>
