<HI>Pity,</HI> i. 39. 125. &verbar; ii. 264. 265 &verbar; iii. 72. Difference in the pity of a man and woman in love-ca&s;es, iii. 237. A pitile&s;s heart de&s;erves not pity, iv. 55. God will pity him who pities his fellow-creature, v. 34. In what ca&s;e a woman in Love may ac<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="apex" EXTENT="1 letter">ept of a man's pity, v. 214. It is the glory of the human heart to melt at another's woe, v. 256. We cannot be angry at the per&s;on whom we pity, v. 263. Who would not &s;o act as to invite the admiration, rather than the pity, of a worthy man? vi. 100. Pity and Love next door neigh|bours, vi. 317.</ITEM>
