<ITEM>S. <HI>Lady Anne,</HI> propo&s;ed to Sir Charles Grandi&s;on for a wife; and has the good wi&s;hes of his Si&s;ters, ii. 241. She makes a vi&s;it at Colnebrook, Mi&s;s Byron pre&s;ent: what pa&s;&s;es in it, ii. 245, 246. Sir Charles's Si&s;ters found him as to his intention with regard to her, ii. 293. She properly rebukes Lady G. for raillying her on her hope|le&s;s Love, iv. 229, 230. More of her, vi. 41. 44, 45. 302.</ITEM>
