<ITEM>SAUNDERS, <HI>Richard,</HI> Sir Charles Grandi&s;on's gentleman, often his almoner, vi. 140, 141. Carries relief to Mrs. Bagenhall from Sir Charles, vi. 215. His and Mrs. Curzon's de&s;cription of the vo|luntary di&s;tinction every-where paid their ma&s;ter, for his goodne&s;s, by people of low degree, vii. 43.</ITEM>
